%N A179580 Number of permutations of {1, ..., n+5} with deficiencies #{i : p(i) < i} exceeding the exceedances #{i : p(i) > i} by n or more.
%C A179580 The sum of the 4 rightmost values in the rows of A062866; e.g. 219 = 146 + 66 + 6 + 1; 534 = 392 + 134 + 7 + 1; 1236 = 960 + 267 + 8 + 1. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 16 2026
%C A179580 We now have a proof for all of the empirical formulas, cf. links. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 17 2026
%C A179580 a(0) added . _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 21 2026
%H A179580 R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A179580/b179580.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100</a>, entries 1..99 from _R. H. Hardin_.
%H A179580 M. F. Hasler and R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A179582/a179582_3.pdf">Hardin's exceedance excesses A179579-A179582</a>, July 2026.
%H A179580 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (8,-26,44,-41,20,-4).
%F A179580 Empirical: a(n) = 8*a(n-1) - 26*a(n-2) + 44*a(n-3) - 41*a(n-4) + 20*a(n-5) - 4*a(n-6);
%F A179580 Empirical: a(n) = (n+5)*(n^2-2*n-36)/6 + (n+7)*2^(n+4). - _R. J. Mathar_, May 26 2016
%F A179580 a(n) = A179579(n+1) + A179572(n). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 16 2026
%F A179580 G.f.: ( 82-437*x+914*x^2-950*x^3+496*x^4-104*x^5 ) / ( (2*x-1)^2*(x-1)^4 ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 22 2026
%o A179580 (PARI) A179580(n) = (n+7)<<(n+4)+(n+5)*(n^2-2*n-36)/6 \\ _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 17 2026
%Y A179580 Cf. A179579 ([n+4]), A179581 ([n+6]), A179582 ([n+7]), A179583 ([n+8]), A179584 ([n+9]).
%Y A179580 Cf. A179571 - A179578 (similar with excess exactly n), A179566 - A179570 (fixed minimum excess), A179564 - A179565 (fixed exact excess).
